  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Poster</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1969</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The centre of the poster shows five stills from the feature film ‘Bitka na Neretvi’ (The battle of Neretva) on a yellow background with the name of its director, Veljko Bulajić. The black bar above displays ‘Kinema Sarajevo’ and the names of the leading actors. The bar on the bottom with a black-and-white background displays the title of the feature in Serbo-Croatian in red, as well as additional technical details.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The war film is situated in Bosnia and Herzegovina in World War II (1943). It is based on a historical confrontation between German and partisan troops. Among the leading actors were Yul Brynner, Orson Welles, Hardy Krüger and Franco Nero. The movie was released in 1969.</ab>
